tag.name: BlankTag
tag.description: Can be used to leave space in a collection. To leave a collection item blank, specify it as a scalar of less than 8 bytes (such as a UINT4), and specify it as embedded.

tag.name: ContainerTag
tag.description: Record-level tag which identifies the container record (always the first one in the file, and there must be only one per file).

tag.name: DataSourceTag
tag.description: Record-level tag which identifies a data source (an instrument, etc.).

tag.name: MonitorSettingsTag
tag.description: Record-level tag which identifies a set of configuration parameters.

tag.name: ObservationTag
tag.description: Record-level tag which identifies an observation -- an event, measurement, etc.

tag.name: VersionInfoTag
tag.description: Specifies the format version for read/write compatibility. The four required numbers in the vector are described below.

tag.name: FileNameTag
tag.description: Original name of the file.

tag.name: CreationTag
tag.description: Date/time when the file was created.

tag.name: LastSavedTag
tag.description: Date/time when the file was last saved.

tag.name: TimesSavedTag
tag.description: The number of times the file has been saved/modified.

tag.name: LanguageTag
tag.description: The language (English, etc.) of the file.

tag.name: TitleTag
tag.description: Arbitrary title.

tag.name: SubjectTag
tag.description: Arbitrary subject string

tag.name: AuthorTag
tag.description: Individual/company who caused the file to be written

tag.name: KeywordsTag
tag.description: Keywords for assisting searches

tag.name: CommentsTag
tag.description: Arbitrary comments

tag.name: LastSavedByTag
tag.description: Individual/company who last wrote to file

tag.name: ApplicationTag
tag.description: Creating application

tag.name: SecurityTag
tag.description: Security descriptor information

tag.name: OwnerTag
tag.description: Owner of file contents (This and some of the following fields are for copyright and trademark information)

tag.name: CopyrightTag
tag.description: Copyright notice

tag.name: TrademarksTag
tag.description: Trademark notice

tag.name: NotesTag
tag.description: RTF formatted notes associated with this file (This corresponds to the IEEE COMTRADE .HDR file, for example).

tag.name: CompressionStyleTag
tag.description: Specified how the compression is applied to the file.

tag.name: CompressionAlgorithmTag
tag.description: Required if tagCompressionStyleID specifies that compression is turned on.

tag.name: CompressionChecksumTag
tag.description: If compression style is _TOTALFILE, this is the checksum for the entire file. This feature has been deprecated under 1.5.

tag.name: NameTag
tag.description: General contact information (all optional)

tag.name: Address1Tag
tag.description: General contact information (all optional)

tag.name: Address2Tag
tag.description: General contact information (all optional)

tag.name: CityTag
tag.description: General contact information (all optional)

tag.name: StateTag
tag.description: General contact information (all optional)

tag.name: PostalCodeTag
tag.description: General contact information (all optional)

tag.name: CountryTag
tag.description: General contact information (all optional)

tag.name: PhoneNumberTag
tag.description: General contact information (all optional)

tag.name: FaxNumberTag
tag.description: General contact information (all optional)

tag.name: EmailTag
tag.description: General contact information (all optional)

tag.name: DataSourceTypeTag
tag.description: Since this ID is a Guid, you can generate a custom ID if a standard ID is not defined.

tag.name: VendorIDTag
tag.description: Since this ID is a Guid, you can generate a custom ID if a standard ID is not defined.

tag.name: EquipmentIDTag
tag.description: Since this ID is a Guid, you can generate a custom ID if a standard ID is not defined.

tag.name: CustomSourceInfoTag
tag.description: This collection can include the standard name, address & telephone number tags -- these apply to the vendor -- as well as tags about the instrument itself.

tag.name: SerialNumberTag
tag.description: Arbitrary string to hold data souce (instrument) serial number

tag.name: DataSourceVersionTag
tag.description: Arbitrary string to hold data souce (instrument) version number (if applicable)

tag.name: DataSourceNameTag
tag.description: Arbitrary string to hold the name of the data souce (instrument)

tag.name: DataSourceOwnerTag
tag.description: Arbitrary string to hold data souce (instrument) owner name

tag.name: DataSourceLocationTag
tag.description: Arbitrary string to hold data souce (instrument) location information

tag.name: DataSourceTimeZoneTag
tag.description: EST, CST, etc.

tag.name: DataSourceCoordinatesTag
tag.description: Longitude/latitude

tag.name: ChannelDefinitionsTag
tag.description: The tagChannelDefns collection must be a collection where the count = the number of channel definitions. Each entry must be another collection, each having the tagOneChannelDefn tag.

tag.name: InstrumentModelNameTag
tag.description: Arbitrary string

tag.name: InstrumentModelNumberTag
tag.description: Arbitrary string

tag.name: OneChannelDefinitionTag
tag.description: Must have one or more channel definitions

tag.name: ChannelNameTag
tag.description: Arbitrary string

tag.name: PhaseIDTag
tag.description: Phase identifier

tag.name: OtherChannelIdentifierTag
tag.description: Arbitrary string

tag.name: GroupNameTag
tag.description: This tag can be repeated if there are multiple groupings. The first one should be the highest-level group (example: a bus), and the next one should be a lower group (example: a feeder).

tag.name: QuantityTypeIDTag
tag.description: The high-level description of the type of quantity which is being captured by this channel. In order to guarantee reader compatibility, the following series value types (in order) should be used (ID_SERIES_VALUE_TYPE_VAL, etc.).

tag.name: QuantityMeasuredIDTag
tag.description: Identifies the physical quantity under measurement -- Voltage, Current, Power, etc. In general, there is a one-to-one correspondence between this and the units of the series, but not always.

tag.name: PhysicalChannelTag
tag.description: The instrument physical channel that this channel definition is associated with.

tag.name: QuantityNameTag
tag.description: Additional quantity information.

tag.name: PrimarySeriesIndexTag
tag.description: Identifies the series which will be the primary. Index into the tagSeriesDefns collection.

tag.name: SeriesDefinitionsTag
tag.description: The tagSeriesDefns collection must be a collection where the count = the number of series definitions. Each entry must be another collection, each having the tagOneSeriesDefn tag.

tag.name: OneSeriesDefinitionTag
tag.description: One of these collections per series.

tag.name: ValueTypeIDTag
tag.description: This specifies the meaning of the series data.

tag.name: QuantityUnitsIDTag
tag.description: This specifies the units of the data in this series. The expected physical type for the tagSeriesValues vector is REAL4 or Real8 (except as noted).

tag.name: QuantityCharacteristicIDTag
tag.description: This specifies additional detail about the meaning of the series data.

tag.name: QuantitySignificantDigitsIDTag
tag.description: Defines the number of significant digits in the data represented by this series.

tag.name: QuantityResolutionIDTag
tag.description: Contains a double indicating the scaled distance between two values of the quantity represented by this series (e.g. scaled A/D resolution)

tag.name: StorageMethodIDTag
tag.description: The legal values for this entry are masks, since they are OR-able.

tag.name: ValueTypeNameTag
tag.description: Arbitrary string

tag.name: ProbabilityIntervalTag
tag.description: For a probability series definition, this specifies its time interval (in seconds; >0).

tag.name: ProbabilityPercentileTag
tag.description: For a probability series definition, this specifies its probability percentile (in percent; 0-100).

tag.name: SeriesNominalQuantityTag
tag.description: Contains the default nominal base voltage or any or any other necessary normalizing quantity. Display programs may use this value or the tagSeriesBaseQuantity in the series instance for displaying data in percent or per unit.

tag.name: EffectiveTag
tag.description: The time that these settings become effective.

tag.name: UseCalibrationTag
tag.description: If TRUE, the calibration adjustments *must* be applied to the series data before using. Otherwise the data is for informative use only.

tag.name: UseTransducerTag
tag.description: If TRUE, the transducer adjustments *must* be applied to the series data before using. Otherwise the data is for informative use only.

tag.name: ChannelSettingsArrayTag
tag.description: Channel specific monitor settings stuff

tag.name: NominalFrequencyTag
tag.description: Nominal power system frequency for this instrument in Hertz

tag.name: SettingPhysicalConnectionTag
tag.description: Identifies the physical connection of the instrumentation or insturment transducers.

tag.name: OneChannelSettingTag
tag.description: One of these collections per channel.

tag.name: ChannelDefinitionIndexTag
tag.description: The channel definition which these settings apply to. Index into tagChannelDefns collection of the matching data source record.

tag.name: TriggerTypeIDTag
tag.description: Integer ID representing which trigger fields are used.

tag.name: FullScaleTag
tag.description: Full scale range for this instrument channel

tag.name: NoiseFloorTag
tag.description: Noise floor for this instrument channel

tag.name: TriggerShapeParametersTag
tag.description: Parameters for shape based triggering algorithms for this channel

tag.name: XDTransformerTypeIDTag
tag.description: PT or CT

tag.name: XDSystemSideRatioTag
tag.description: System side part of ratio

tag.name: XDMonitorSideRatioTag
tag.description: Monitor side part of ratio

tag.name: XDFrequencyResponseTag
tag.description: Transducer frequency response

tag.name: CalTimeSkewTag
tag.description: Chanel time skew

tag.name: CalOffsetTag
tag.description: Channel DC offset error

tag.name: CalRatioTag
tag.description: Channel ratio error

tag.name: CalMustUseARCalTag
tag.description: Flag indicating that the applied/recordedt calibration arrays must be used to correct data.

tag.name: CalAppliedTag
tag.description: Array of applied signals for this channel

tag.name: CalRecordedTag
tag.description: Array of recorded actual values for the applied signal

tag.name: TriggerHighHighTag
tag.description: High High trigger for this channel

tag.name: TriggerHighTag
tag.description: High trigger for this channel

tag.name: TriggerLowTag
tag.description: Low trigger for this channel

tag.name: TriggerLowLowTag
tag.description: Low Low trigger for this channel

tag.name: TriggerDeadbandTag
tag.description: Deadband trigger for this channel

tag.name: TriggerRateTag
tag.description: Rate of change trigger for this channel

tag.name: ObservationNameTag
tag.description: Name of the observation

tag.name: TimeCreateTag
tag.description: Time this observation was created

tag.name: TimeStartTag
tag.description: The start time of the observation -- the zero point where the .

tag.name: TriggerMethodTag
tag.description: Type of trigger which caused the observation.

tag.name: TimeTriggeredTag
tag.description: Tme this observation was triggered if appropriate

tag.name: ChannelTriggerIndexTag
tag.description: Index into tagChannelInstances collection within this record. This specifies which channel(s) initiated the observation.

tag.name: ObservationSerialTag
tag.description: The serial number of the observation (if generated by an instrument, for example).

tag.name: ObservationAggregationSerialTag
tag.description: Serial number -- of specific cycle, for example -- that can be used to correlate observations.

tag.name: DisturbanceCategoryIDTag
tag.description: Currently uses the IEEE 1159 disturbance categories, but others could be used as well.

tag.name: ChannelInstancesTag
tag.description: This collection contains a set of channel instances. It is not required to contain the same number of channels as there are channel instances. This can be determined on an observation-by-observation basis.

tag.name: CharacterizationDisturbanceDirectionTag
tag.description: Direction of disturbance represented by the data in this observation. Value of 0 means don't know, 1 means originated from load side, 2 means originated from source side.

tag.name: CharacterizationDisturbanceDirectionQualityTag
tag.description: Quality of the direction result given in another tag. Range is from 0 (no confidence), to 100 (darn sure).

tag.name: OneChannelInstanceTag
tag.description: One of these collections per channel instance.

tag.name: CharacterizationDurationTag
tag.description: Simple characterization value: duration of disturbance (seconds)

tag.name: SeriesInstancesTag
tag.description: This collection must contain the exact number of series which were defined for the specified channel definition.

tag.name: CharacterizationMagnitudeTag
tag.description: Simple characterization value: magnitude of disturbance (percent: 100%=nominal)

tag.name: CharacterizationFrequencyTag
tag.description: Simple characterization value: frequency (Hertz)

tag.name: ChannelTriggerModuleInfoTag
tag.description: Contains a 32 bit integer that represents module spefic information related to the trigger reason.

tag.name: ChannelTriggerModuleNameTag
tag.description: Contains the name of a device specific code or hardware module, algorithm or rule not necessarily channel based that caused this channel to be recorded

tag.name: CrossTriggerDeviceNameTag
tag.description: Contains the name of the device involved in an external cross trigger scenario.

tag.name: CrossTriggerChannelIndexTag
tag.description: Contains the channel definition index of the channel that triggered in a cross trigger scenrio.

tag.name: ChannelTriggerTypeIDTag
tag.description: Integer ID representing the trigger type for this channel instance. Used only with type ID_QT_VALUELOG wit a trigger method of channel.

tag.name: ChannelFrequencyTag
tag.description: For a channel which contains multiple instances to represent a sparse log of time-stamped frequency-domain information, this specifies the frequency for which this channel instance applies (in Hertz). If not present, the channel characteristics are frequency independent unless further specified by the quantity characteristic.

tag.name: ChannelGroupIDTag
tag.description: For a channel which contains multiple instances to represent a sparse log of time-stamped frequency-domain information, this specifies the frequency for which this channel instance applies (in Index). The index referes to a harmonic or interharmonic group index.

tag.name: OneSeriesInstanceTag
tag.description: One of these collections per series instance.

tag.name: SeriesBaseQuantityTag
tag.description: Contains the nominal base voltage, or any other necessary normalizing quantity.

tag.name: SeriesScaleTag
tag.description: If not present, assumed to be 1. The physical type should match that of tagSeriesValues.

tag.name: SeriesOffsetTag
tag.description: If not present, assumed to be 0. Generally used as a starting point when the ID_SERIES_METHOD_INCREMENT storage method is used. The physical type should match that of tagSeriesValues.

tag.name: SeriesShareChannelIndexTag
tag.description: Identifies the channel which owns the series to be shared. An index into the tagChannelInstances collection.

tag.name: SeriesShareSeriesIndexTag
tag.description: Identifies the series to be shared. An index into the tagSeriesInstances collection. The tagSeriesValues vector from this series is used. This must be present if tagSeriesShareChannelIdx is used.

tag.name: SeriesValuesTag
tag.description: Contains the actual data points of the series. Required unless the data series is shared, in which case both tagSeriesShareChannelIdx and tagSeriesShareSeriesIdx should be present.

id.name: RecordLevel
id.description: The body of each record is compressed individually. The checksums will be found in the header of each record.

id.name: TotalFile
id.description: Everything after the container record is compressed as a single block. This feature has been deprecated under 1.5 and should not be used.

id.name: Zlib
id.description: A standard compression algorithm -- ZLIB -- standardized by the IETF (Internet Engineering Task Force). See http://quest.jpl.nasa.gov/zlib/ for details.

id.name: PKZIP
id.description: A commercial package, the PKZIP data compression library, was used to compress the data. This feature has been deprecated under 1.5 and should not be used.

id.name: Residual
id.description: Residual - the vector or point-on-wave sum of Phases A, B, and C. Should be zero in a perfectly balanced system.

id.name: Net
id.description: Net - the vector or point-on-wave sum of Phases A, B, C and the Neutral phase. Should be zero in a 4 wire system with no earth return path.

id.name: Total
id.description: The value representing a total or other summarizing value in a multi-phase system.

id.name: LineToNeutralAverage
id.description: The value representing average of 3 line-neutral values

id.name: LineToLineAverage
id.description: The value representing average of 3 line-line values

id.name: Worst
id.description: The value representing the "worst" of the 3 phases

id.name: ValueLog
id.description: TIME, MIN, MAX, AVG, INST, VAL ? / For time-based logged entries.

id.name: Phasor
id.description: TIME, MIN, MAX, AVG, INST, VAL, PHASEANGLE ? / For time-domain measurements including magnitudes and (optionally) phase angle.

id.name: Response
id.description: VAL (FREQUENCY), VAL, PHASEANGLE / For frequency-domain measurements including magnitude and (optionally) phase angle.

id.name: Flash
id.description: TIME, LAT, LON, VAL, POLARITY, ELLIPSE

id.name: Histogram3D
id.description: XBINLOW, XBINHIGH, YBINLOW, YBINHIGH, BINID, COUNT

id.name: CPF
id.description: PROB, VAL. (Note that the specific P1 value types have been deprecated.)

id.name: Seconds
id.description: Seconds -- relative from the beginning time of the observation (using tagTimeStart as the beginning time).

id.name: Timestamp
id.description: Absolute time. Each timestamp in the series must be in absolute time using the TIMESTAMPPQDIF physical type. This is generally *not* recommended, but is acceptible when _VALUELOG is used.

id.name: Cycles
id.description: The timestamps are in cycles, relative to tagTimeStart.

id.name: Values
id.description: This should be the default value type for a measurement -- a value.

id.name: Phase Angle
id.description: Phase angle (used for a _VAL series or when it applies to all).

id.name: Phase Angle Mininum
id.description: Phase angle which corresponds to a _MIN series (completing a complex pair).

id.name: Phase Angle Maximum
id.description: Phase angle which corresponds to a _MAX series.

id.name: Phase Angle Average
id.description: Phase angle which corresponds to an _AVG series.

id.name: Area
id.description: Area under the signal, usually an rms voltage, current or other quantity.

id.name: Transition
id.description: Transition event code series. This series contains codes cooresponding to values in a value series that indicates what kind of transition caused the event to be recorded. Used only with VALUELOG data.

id.name: Probability: 1%
id.description: Probability: 1%. This has been deprecated under 1.5 and should not be used.

id.name: Probability: 5%
id.description: Probability: 5%. This has been deprecated under 1.5 and should not be used.

id.name: Probability: 10%
id.description: Probability: 10%. This has been deprecated under 1.5 and should not be used.

id.name: Probability: 90%
id.description: Probability: 90%. This has been deprecated under 1.5 and should not be used.

id.name: Probability: 95%
id.description: Probability: 95%. This has been deprecated under 1.5 and should not be used.

id.name: Probability: 99%
id.description: Probability: 99%. This has been deprecated under 1.5 and should not be used.

id.name: Frequency
id.description: Frequency. This has been deprecated under 1.5 and should not be used. (It is now a characteristic instead of a value type.)

id.name: Values
id.description: The data in tagSeriesValues are a straight array of data points.

id.name: Scaled
id.description: All values in tagSeriesValues will be multiplied by tagSeriesScale.

id.name: Increment
id.description: The data in tagSeriesValues consists of a special sequence to indicate the contents of a regular rate series (see main documentation for details). The vector contains: #rates, numpts1, rate1 ... numptsN, rateN.
